---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Getting Started"
  description="Install Harbor and scaffold your first Rust DDD project in under a minute."
>
  <div class="min-h-screen pt-20">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-16 lg:grid lg:grid-cols-[240px_1fr] lg:gap-12">

      <!-- Sidebar -->
      <aside class="hidden lg:block">
        <nav class="sticky top-28 space-y-1" aria-label="Documentation navigation">
          <p class="mb-3 font-mono text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-harbor-mist/50">Getting Started</p>
          <a href="#installation" class="doc-link block rounded px-3 py-1.5 font-sans text-sm text-harbor-mist transition-colors hover:bg-harbor-navy hover:text-harbor-ice">Installation</a>
          <a href="#new-project" class="doc-link block rounded px-3 py-1.5 font-sans text-sm text-harbor-mist transition-colors hover:bg-harbor-navy hover:text-harbor-ice">New Project</a>
          <a href="#scaffold" class="doc-link block rounded px-3 py-1.5 font-sans text-sm text-harbor-mist transition-colors hover:bg-harbor-navy hover:text-harbor-ice">Generate Scaffold</a>
          <a href="#layer-generators" class="doc-link block rounded px-3 py-1.5 font-sans text-sm text-harbor-mist transition-colors hover:bg-harbor-navy hover:text-harbor-ice">Layer Generators</a>
          <a href="#use-case" class="doc-link block rounded px-3 py-1.5 font-sans text-sm text-harbor-mist transition-colors hover:bg-harbor-navy hover:text-harbor-ice">Add Use Case</a>
          <a href="#database" class="doc-link block rounded px-3 py-1.5 font-sans text-sm text-harbor-mist transition-colors hover:bg-harbor-navy hover:text-harbor-ice">Database (SQLx)</a>
          <a href="#architecture" class="doc-link block rounded px-3 py-1.5 font-sans text-sm text-harbor-mist transition-colors hover:bg-harbor-navy hover:text-harbor-ice">Architecture</a>
          <a href="#snippets" class="doc-link block rounded px-3 py-1.5 font-sans text-sm text-harbor-mist transition-colors hover:bg-harbor-navy hover:text-harbor-ice">IDE Snippets</a>
        </nav>
      </aside>

      <!-- Content -->
      <article class="prose-harbor min-w-0">
        <h1 class="font-mono text-4xl font-bold text-harbor-ice lg:text-5xl">Getting Started</h1>
        <p class="mt-4 font-sans text-lg text-harbor-mist">
          Harbor is a CLI tool that scaffolds production-ready Rust backends with Domain-Driven Design architecture. From install to running API in under a minute.
        </p>

        <!-- Prerequisites -->
        <div class="mt-8 rounded-md border border-harbor-teal/30 bg-harbor-teal/5 px-5 py-4">
          <p class="font-mono text-sm font-semibold text-harbor-teal">Prerequisites</p>
          <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1 font-sans text-sm text-harbor-mist">
            <li>Rust stable (1.85+) — <a href="https://rustup.rs" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-harbor-teal hover:underline">install via rustup</a></li>
            <li>Cargo (included with Rust)</li>
            <li>Optional: PostgreSQL + SQLx CLI for database projects</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Installation -->
        <section id="installation" class="mt-16 scroll-mt-28">
          <h2 class="font-mono text-2xl font-bold text-harbor-ice">Installation</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 font-sans text-harbor-mist">Install the Harbor CLI from crates.io:</p>
          <div class="code-block mt-4 flex items-center gap-3 rounded-md border border-harbor-steel/40 border-l-4 border-l-harbor-teal bg-harbor-navy px-5 py-4">
            <span class="font-mono text-sm text-harbor-teal select-none">$</span>
            <code class="font-mono text-sm text-harbor-ice">cargo install harbor-framework</code>
            <button class="copy-btn ml-auto cursor-pointer text-harbor-mist hover:text-harbor-ice" data-copy="cargo install harbor-framework" aria-label="Copy">
              <svg class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8 16H6a2 2 0 01-2-2V6a2 2 0 012-2h8a2 2 0 012 2v2m-6 12h8a2 2 0 002-2v-8a2 2 0 00-2-2h-8a2 2 0 00-2 2v8a2 2 0 002 2z"/></svg>
            </button>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-4 font-sans text-sm text-harbor-mist">Verify the installation:</p>
          <div class="code-block mt-2 flex items-center gap-3 rounded-md border border-harbor-steel/40 bg-harbor-navy px-5 py-4">
            <span class="font-mono text-sm text-harbor-teal select-none">$</span>
            <code class="font-mono text-sm text-harbor-ice">harbor --version</code>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- New Project -->
        <section id="new-project" class="mt-16 scroll-mt-28">
          <h2 class="font-mono text-2xl font-bold text-harbor-ice">New Project</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 font-sans text-harbor-mist">
            Create a new Harbor workspace. The interactive wizard asks for your project name, whether you need database support, and whether to include the Greeting demo entity.
          </p>
          <div class="code-block mt-4 flex items-center gap-3 rounded-md border border-harbor-steel/40 border-l-4 border-l-harbor-teal bg-harbor-navy px-5 py-4">
            <span class="font-mono text-sm text-harbor-teal select-none">$</span>
            <code class="font-mono text-sm text-harbor-ice">harbor new my-app</code>
            <button class="copy-btn ml-auto cursor-pointer text-harbor-mist hover:text-harbor-ice" data-copy="harbor new my-app" aria-label="Copy">
              <svg class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8 16H6a2 2 0 01-2-2V6a2 2 0 012-2h8a2 2 0 012 2v2m-6 12h8a2 2 0 002-2v-8a2 2 0 00-2-2h-8a2 2 0 00-2 2v8a2 2 0 002 2z"/></svg>
            </button>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-4 font-sans text-sm text-harbor-mist">For non-interactive use (CI/scripts):</p>
          <div class="code-block mt-2 flex items-center gap-3 rounded-md border border-harbor-steel/40 bg-harbor-navy px-5 py-4">
            <span class="font-mono text-sm text-harbor-teal select-none">$</span>
            <code class="font-mono text-sm text-harbor-ice">harbor new --name my-app --db --no-demo</code>
          </div>

          <p class="mt-6 font-sans text-sm font-semibold text-harbor-ice">Generated structure:</p>
          <div class="mt-3 rounded-md border border-harbor-steel/40 bg-harbor-navy p-5 font-mono text-sm leading-relaxed">
            <div class="text-harbor-mist/60">my-app/</div>
            <div class="pl-4"><span class="text-harbor-teal">business/</span><span class="text-harbor-mist/40 ml-3">← domain + application</span></div>
            <div class="pl-8 text-harbor-mist/50">src/domain/greeting/</div>
            <div class="pl-8 text-harbor-mist/50">src/application/greeting/</div>
            <div class="pl-4 mt-1"><span class="text-harbor-indigo">infrastructure/</span><span class="text-harbor-mist/40 ml-3">← adapters</span></div>
            <div class="pl-8 text-harbor-mist/50">src/greeting/repository.rs</div>
            <div class="pl-4 mt-1"><span class="text-harbor-rust">presentation/</span><span class="text-harbor-mist/40 ml-3">← http api</span></div>
            <div class="pl-8 text-harbor-mist/50">src/api/greeting/routes.rs</div>
            <div class="pl-4 mt-1 text-harbor-mist/50">harbor.toml</div>
            <div class="pl-4 text-harbor-mist/50">Cargo.toml</div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Scaffold -->
        <section id="scaffold" class="mt-16 scroll-mt-28">
          <h2 class="font-mono text-2xl font-bold text-harbor-ice">Generate Scaffold</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 font-sans text-harbor-mist">
            Scaffold a complete DDD entity across all layers. Harbor creates the domain model, repository trait, use cases, infrastructure adapter, and presentation routes — wired together automatically.
          </p>
          <div class="code-block mt-4 flex items-center gap-3 rounded-md border border-harbor-steel/40 border-l-4 border-l-harbor-teal bg-harbor-navy px-5 py-4">
            <span class="font-mono text-sm text-harbor-teal select-none">$</span>
            <code class="font-mono text-sm text-harbor-ice">harbor generate scaffold User</code>
            <button class="copy-btn ml-auto cursor-pointer text-harbor-mist hover:text-harbor-ice" data-copy="harbor generate scaffold User" aria-label="Copy">
              <svg class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8 16H6a2 2 0 01-2-2V6a2 2 0 012-2h8a2 2 0 012 2v2m-6 12h8a2 2 0 002-2v-8a2 2 0 00-2-2h-8a2 2 0 00-2 2v8a2 2 0 002 2z"/></svg>
            </button>
          </div>

          <p class="mt-6 font-sans text-sm font-semibold text-harbor-ice">What gets created:</p>
          <div class="mt-3 space-y-2 font-sans text-sm text-harbor-mist">
            <div class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-harbor-teal font-mono">business/</span><span>model.rs, errors.rs, repository.rs (trait + mockall mock), 5 use cases (create, get, list, update, delete)</span></div>
            <div class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-harbor-indigo font-mono">infrastructure/</span><span>repository (InMemory or Pg — inferred from harbor.toml)</span></div>
            <div class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-harbor-rust font-mono">presentation/</span><span>routes.rs, dto.rs, responses.rs, error_mapper.rs</span></div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Layer Generators -->
        <section id="layer-generators" class="mt-16 scroll-mt-28">
          <h2 class="font-mono text-2xl font-bold text-harbor-ice">Layer Generators</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 font-sans text-harbor-mist">
            Generate one DDD layer at a time. Ideal for AI-assisted development — keeping each agent focused on a single layer prevents context drift and makes compiler errors immediately actionable.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-5 space-y-3">
            <div class="code-block flex items-center gap-3 rounded-md border border-harbor-steel/40 border-l-4 border-l-harbor-teal bg-harbor-navy px-5 py-4">
              <span class="font-mono text-sm text-harbor-teal select-none">$</span>
              <code class="font-mono text-sm text-harbor-ice">harbor generate domain Product</code>
              <button class="copy-btn ml-auto cursor-pointer text-harbor-mist hover:text-harbor-ice" data-copy="harbor generate domain Product" aria-label="Copy">
                <svg class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8 16H6a2 2 0 01-2-2V6a2 2 0 012-2h8a2 2 0 012 2v2m-6 12h8a2 2 0 002-2v-8a2 2 0 00-2-2h-8a2 2 0 00-2 2v8a2 2 0 002 2z"/></svg>
              </button>
            </div>
            <div class="code-block flex items-center gap-3 rounded-md border border-harbor-steel/40 border-l-4 border-l-harbor-teal bg-harbor-navy px-5 py-4">
              <span class="font-mono text-sm text-harbor-teal select-none">$</span>
              <code class="font-mono text-sm text-harbor-ice">harbor generate application Product</code>
              <button class="copy-btn ml-auto cursor-pointer text-harbor-mist hover:text-harbor-ice" data-copy="harbor generate application Product" aria-label="Copy">
                <svg class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8 16H6a2 2 0 01-2-2V6a2 2 0 012-2h8a2 2 0 012 2v2m-6 12h8a2 2 0 002-2v-8a2 2 0 00-2-2h-8a2 2 0 00-2 2v8a2 2 0 002 2z"/></svg>
              </button>
            </div>
            <div class="code-block flex items-center gap-3 rounded-md border border-harbor-steel/40 border-l-4 border-l-harbor-indigo bg-harbor-navy px-5 py-4">
              <span class="font-mono text-sm text-harbor-teal select-none">$</span>
              <code class="font-mono text-sm text-harbor-ice">harbor generate repository Product</code>
              <button class="copy-btn ml-auto cursor-pointer text-harbor-mist hover:text-harbor-ice" data-copy="harbor generate repository Product" aria-label="Copy">
                <svg class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8 16H6a2 2 0 01-2-2V6a2 2 0 012-2h8a2 2 0 012 2v2m-6 12h8a2 2 0 002-2v-8a2 2 0 00-2-2h-8a2 2 0 00-2 2v8a2 2 0 002 2z"/></svg>
              </button>
            </div>
            <div class="code-block flex items-center gap-3 rounded-md border border-harbor-steel/40 border-l-4 border-l-harbor-rust bg-harbor-navy px-5 py-4">
              <span class="font-mono text-sm text-harbor-teal select-none">$</span>
              <code class="font-mono text-sm text-harbor-ice">harbor generate presentation Product</code>
              <button class="copy-btn ml-auto cursor-pointer text-harbor-mist hover:text-harbor-ice" data-copy="harbor generate presentation Product" aria-label="Copy">
                <svg class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8 16H6a2 2 0 01-2-2V6a2 2 0 012-2h8a2 2 0 012 2v2m-6 12h8a2 2 0 002-2v-8a2 2 0 00-2-2h-8a2 2 0 00-2 2v8a2 2 0 002 2z"/></svg>
              </button>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-6 space-y-2 font-sans text-sm text-harbor-mist">
            <div class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-harbor-teal font-mono flex-none">domain</span><span>model, errors, repository trait, 5 use case traits, <span class="text-harbor-indigo font-mono">ProductMother</span> (Object Mother) — registers entity in harbor.toml</span></div>
            <div class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-harbor-teal font-mono flex-none">application</span><span>5 use case implementations with unit tests</span></div>
            <div class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-harbor-indigo font-mono flex-none">repository</span><span>InMemory or Pg adapter — inferred from <span class="font-mono text-xs text-harbor-rust">harbor.toml</span></span></div>
            <div class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-harbor-rust font-mono flex-none">presentation</span><span>routes, dto, responses, error mapper — regenerates <span class="font-mono text-xs">bootstrap.rs</span></span></div>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-5 font-sans text-sm text-harbor-mist">
            Each command validates the prior step completed and prints a <span class="font-mono text-xs text-harbor-teal">Next:</span> hint. Use <code class="font-mono text-xs text-harbor-ice">harbor generate scaffold</code> when you want all layers at once.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Use Case -->
        <section id="use-case" class="mt-16 scroll-mt-28">
          <h2 class="font-mono text-2xl font-bold text-harbor-ice">Add a Use Case</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 font-sans text-harbor-mist">
            Add a single use case to an existing entity. Harbor generates the trait, implementation, and unit tests.
          </p>
          <div class="code-block mt-4 flex items-center gap-3 rounded-md border border-harbor-steel/40 border-l-4 border-l-harbor-teal bg-harbor-navy px-5 py-4">
            <span class="font-mono text-sm text-harbor-teal select-none">$</span>
            <code class="font-mono text-sm text-harbor-ice">harbor generate use-case User create</code>
            <button class="copy-btn ml-auto cursor-pointer text-harbor-mist hover:text-harbor-ice" data-copy="harbor generate use-case User create" aria-label="Copy">
              <svg class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8 16H6a2 2 0 01-2-2V6a2 2 0 012-2h8a2 2 0 012 2v2m-6 12h8a2 2 0 002-2v-8a2 2 0 00-2-2h-8a2 2 0 00-2 2v8a2 2 0 002 2z"/></svg>
            </button>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Database -->
        <section id="database" class="mt-16 scroll-mt-28">
          <h2 class="font-mono text-2xl font-bold text-harbor-ice">Database (SQLx)</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 font-sans text-harbor-mist">
            Harbor has first-class SQLx + Postgres support. Enable it when creating a project — Harbor infers the choice for every subsequent scaffold automatically.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-4 space-y-3">
            <div class="code-block flex items-center gap-3 rounded-md border border-harbor-steel/40 border-l-4 border-l-harbor-indigo bg-harbor-navy px-5 py-4">
              <span class="font-mono text-sm text-harbor-teal select-none">$</span>
              <code class="font-mono text-sm text-harbor-ice">harbor new --name my-app --db</code>
            </div>
            <div class="code-block flex items-center gap-3 rounded-md border border-harbor-steel/40 border-l-4 border-l-harbor-indigo bg-harbor-navy px-5 py-4">
              <span class="font-mono text-sm text-harbor-teal select-none">$</span>
              <code class="font-mono text-sm text-harbor-ice">harbor generate scaffold User</code>
            </div>
            <div class="code-block flex items-center gap-3 rounded-md border border-harbor-steel/40 bg-harbor-navy px-5 py-4">
              <span class="font-mono text-sm text-harbor-teal select-none">$</span>
              <code class="font-mono text-sm text-harbor-ice">harbor generate migration create_users_table</code>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-4 font-sans text-sm text-harbor-mist">
            Harbor reads <code class="font-mono text-xs text-harbor-rust">harbor.toml</code> to decide: db projects get a <code class="font-mono text-xs text-harbor-mist">PgUserRepository</code> with a connection pool and auto-created migration; non-db projects get <code class="font-mono text-xs text-harbor-mist">InMemoryUserRepository</code>. No flag needed on every scaffold.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Architecture -->
        <section id="architecture" class="mt-16 scroll-mt-28">
          <h2 class="font-mono text-2xl font-bold text-harbor-ice">Architecture</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 font-sans text-harbor-mist">
            Harbor enforces a strict dependency rule: dependencies only point inward. The domain layer has zero external dependencies.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-6 rounded-md border border-harbor-steel/40 bg-harbor-navy p-6 font-mono text-sm">
            <div class="text-harbor-mist/50 text-xs mb-4">dependency flow (inward only)</div>
            <div class="space-y-2">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                <span class="w-36 text-harbor-rust">presentation/</span>
                <span class="text-harbor-mist/40">→ depends on</span>
                <span class="text-harbor-indigo">infrastructure/</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                <span class="w-36 text-harbor-indigo">infrastructure/</span>
                <span class="text-harbor-mist/40">→ depends on</span>
                <span class="text-harbor-teal">business/</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                <span class="w-36 text-harbor-teal">business/</span>
                <span class="text-harbor-mist/40">→ depends on</span>
                <span class="text-harbor-mist/60">nothing (std + thiserror only)</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- IDE Snippets -->
        <section id="snippets" class="mt-16 scroll-mt-28">
          <h2 class="font-mono text-2xl font-bold text-harbor-ice">IDE Snippets</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 font-sans text-harbor-mist">
            Every <code class="font-mono text-xs text-harbor-teal">harbor new</code> project ships with 23 Harbor-adapted Rust snippets for Zed, VS Code, and nvim+LuaSnip. No configuration needed — files are written automatically and loaded by your editor from the project root.
          </p>

          <!-- IDE setup -->
          <div class="mt-6 space-y-3">
            <div class="rounded-md border border-harbor-teal/20 bg-harbor-navy p-4">
              <p class="font-mono text-sm font-semibold text-harbor-teal">Zed</p>
              <p class="mt-1 font-sans text-sm text-harbor-mist">
                Snippets are written to <code class="font-mono text-xs text-harbor-teal">.zed/snippets/rust.json</code>. Zed loads project-local snippets automatically — no further setup.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-md border border-harbor-steel/30 bg-harbor-navy p-4">
              <p class="font-mono text-sm font-semibold text-harbor-ice">VS Code</p>
              <p class="mt-1 font-sans text-sm text-harbor-mist">
                Snippets are written to <code class="font-mono text-xs text-harbor-mist">.vscode/harbor.code-snippets</code>. VS Code picks up workspace snippet files automatically.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-md border border-harbor-steel/30 bg-harbor-navy p-4">
              <p class="font-mono text-sm font-semibold text-harbor-ice">nvim + LuaSnip</p>
              <p class="mt-1 font-sans text-sm text-harbor-mist">
                The VS Code file uses TextMate format, which LuaSnip can load directly. Add to your config:
              </p>
              <div class="mt-3 rounded bg-harbor-deep px-4 py-3">
                <code class="font-mono text-xs text-harbor-mist/80">{"require(\"luasnip.loaders.from_vscode\").lazy_load({ paths = {\"./.vscode\"} })"}</code>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Snippet table -->
          <p class="mt-8 font-sans text-sm font-semibold text-harbor-ice">Available snippets</p>
          <div class="mt-3 space-y-6">
            <!-- Domain -->
            <div>
              <div class="mb-2 flex items-center gap-2">
                <span class="font-mono text-xs font-bold text-harbor-teal uppercase tracking-widest">Domain</span>
                <div class="h-px flex-1 bg-harbor-steel/30"></div>
              </div>
              <div class="space-y-1.5">
                <div class="flex items-start gap-3 rounded border border-harbor-steel/20 bg-harbor-navy px-4 py-2">
                  <code class="w-44 flex-none font-mono text-xs text-harbor-teal">domain-model</code>
                  <span class="font-sans text-xs text-harbor-mist/70">Entity struct + Props + new(props) + from_repository()</span>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-start gap-3 rounded border border-harbor-steel/20 bg-harbor-navy px-4 py-2">
                  <code class="w-44 flex-none font-mono text-xs text-harbor-teal">domain-errors</code>
                  <span class="font-sans text-xs text-harbor-mist/70">thiserror enum with machine-readable error codes</span>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-start gap-3 rounded border border-harbor-steel/20 bg-harbor-navy px-4 py-2">
                  <code class="w-44 flex-none font-mono text-xs text-harbor-teal">repository-trait</code>
                  <span class="font-sans text-xs text-harbor-mist/70">RepositoryTrait + mockall mock in pub mod mocks</span>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-start gap-3 rounded border border-harbor-steel/20 bg-harbor-navy px-4 py-2">
                  <code class="w-44 flex-none font-mono text-xs text-harbor-teal">domain-use-case</code>
